  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The model must satisfy a peak shear-stress exposure limit of 150 Pa·s cumulative dose to bound sub-lethal red blood cell damage across all five flow-speed operating points; this constraint is explicitly identified in the COU narrative as a binding safety obligation for patient protection during extended CPB runs.",
