    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "Morrison COU1 Requirement Set v1",
    "description": "Requirements binding the CFD hemolysis credibility assessment for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. REQ-01: The computational model shall predict relative hemolysis index (RHI) with a maximum allowable deviation of 15% from in-vitro reference measurements across all five operating points. REQ-02: Mesh discretization error shall be quantified via Richardson extrapolation and shall not exceed 5% GCI for the primary quantity of interest. REQ-03: The SST k-omega turbulence closure shall be verified against at least one published velocity dataset for a geometrically similar centrifugal pump. REQ-04: All CFD software shall be operated under a documented quality assurance plan meeting ASME V&V 10.1 guidance. REQ-05: Operating conditions used in validation shall span the full intended clinical flow-rate range of 2–6 L/min.",
